# AEGIS OSS

Open-source distribution of the AEGIS cognitive kernel framework.

> This project uses [ADF](https://github.com/Stackbilt-dev/charter) for AI agent context management.
> All stack rules, constraints, and architectural guidance live in `.ai/`.

## Context

This is the **public OSS repo** — a deployable framework extracted from the production AEGIS system.
The production AEGIS instance (private `Stackbilt-dev/aegis` repo) has additional integrations,
Stackbilt-specific bindings, and proprietary features not included here.

This repo should be approachable by developers who have never seen AEGIS before.

## Key Principles

- **Self-contained**: Everything needed to deploy lives in this repo. No hidden dependencies.
- **Documented**: Every feature referenced in README/docs must actually exist in the codebase.
- **No internal leaks**: No Stackbilt account IDs, tokens, internal URLs, or proprietary service references.
- **Approachable**: Code comments and docs assume the reader is new to AEGIS.

## Structure

```
aegis-oss/
  .ai/              # ADF agent context files
  docs/             # User-facing documentation
  scripts/          # Deploy, hooks, taskrunner
  web/              # Cloudflare Worker (the actual framework)
    src/            # TypeScript source
    tests/          # Vitest test suite
    schema.sql      # D1 database schema
    wrangler.toml.example  # Template config
```

## Commands

```bash
cd web

# Install deps
npm install

# Run tests
npm test

# Typecheck
npm run typecheck

# Local dev
npx wrangler dev

# Deploy
npx wrangler deploy
```

## What NOT to commit

- `web/wrangler.toml` (contains account-specific IDs) — use `wrangler.toml.example`
- `web/src/operator/config.ts` / `persona.ts` (user customizations) — use `.example` files
- `.dev.vars` (secrets)
- Any Stackbilt-specific account IDs, tokens, or internal URLs

## Docs

All docs referenced in README.md must exist in `docs/`. Currently:
- `docs/getting-started.md` — Quick start walkthrough
- `docs/architecture.md` — System architecture and design decisions
- `docs/configuration.md` — Full operator config reference
- `docs/memory-system.md` — Memory tiers, consolidation, and dreaming cycle

## Versioning

- Version tracked in `web/src/version.ts`
- Use semver: patch for fixes, minor for features, major for breaking changes
